---------
निश्शेष-विश्व-रचना च
the creation of the whole universe
कटाक्ष-मोक्ष:
is by extending a glance of Thy eye
कर्णौ दिश: -
(Thy) ears are the directions (quarters)
अश्वियुगलम्
the two Ashvinidevas
तव नासिके द्वे
are Thy two nostrils
लोभत्रपे च
greed and modesty
भगवन्
O Lord!
अधर-उत्तर-ओष्ठौ
(are Thy) lower and upper lips
तारा-गणा: - च
and the galaxy of stars
दशना:
are Thy teeth
शमन: च दंष्ट्रा
the molars are Yama (the god of death)

s16
00:03:49.166 --> 00:04:12.666 align:start
O Lord! The whole of the creation is the extension of Thy one glance. The different directions are Thy ears. The Ashwini devataas are Thy two nostrils. Greed and modesty are Thy lower lip and the upper lip.The stars are Thy teeth, and Yama (death) is Thy molars.
---------
